```

### Layout & Routing

```text
Layout:
  render():
    show:
      - header / navbar
      - <Routers /> (main content)
      - footer
```

```text
Routers:
  define ProtectedRoute(children):
    if auth.loading:
      show full-screen "Loading..."
    else if auth.isAuthenticated:
      return children
    else:
      redirect to "/login"

  define PublicRoute(children, redirectIfAuth = true):
    if auth.loading:
      show full-screen "Loading..."
    else if redirectIfAuth AND auth.isAuthenticated:
      redirect to "/dashboard"
    else:
      return children

  define RoleBasedDashboard():
    if user.role == "admin":   return <AdminDashboard />
    if user.role == "mentor":  return <MentorDashboard />
    else:                      return <UserDashboard />

  routes:
    "/"             -> <Home />
    "/login"        -> <PublicRoute><Login /></PublicRoute>
    "/signup"       -> <PublicRoute><Login /></PublicRoute>
    "/dashboard"    -> <ProtectedRoute><RoleBasedDashboard /></ProtectedRoute>
    "/chat"         -> <ProtectedRoute><ChatPage /></ProtectedRoute>
    "/resume"       -> <ProtectedRoute><ResumePage /></ProtectedRoute>
    "/resources"    -> <ProtectedRoute><ResourcesPage /></ProtectedRoute>
    "/wellness"     -> <ProtectedRoute><WellnessPage /></ProtectedRoute>
    "/study-groups" -> <ProtectedRoute><StudyGroupsPage /></ProtectedRoute>
    "/achievements" -> <ProtectedRoute><AchievementsPage /></ProtectedRoute>
    "/edit-profile" -> <ProtectedRoute><EditProfile /></ProtectedRoute>
    "/ats-score"    -> <ProtectedRoute><ATSScorePage /></ProtectedRoute>
    "*"             -> redirect to "/"
```

### Auth Context

```text
AuthProvider:
  state:
    user            // user object or null
    isAuthenticated // bool
    loading         // bool while checking token

  onMount():
    set loading = true
    token = localStorage["token"]
    if token exists:
      try:
        resp = authService.getCurrentUser()
        if resp.success:
          user = resp.data.user (+ first_login flag)
          isAuthenticated = true
        else:
          logout()
      catch:
        logout()
    set loading = false

  login(userData, token, firstLoginFlag):
    user = userData + { first_login: firstLoginFlag }
    isAuthenticated = true
    if token:
      localStorage["token"] = token

  logout():
    user = null
    isAuthenticated = false
    remove token from localStorage

  provide { user, loading, isAuthenticated, login, logout } via context
```

### API Client & Auth Services

```text
API_URL:
  raw = env.VITE_API_URL or "http://localhost:5000/api"
  if raw ends with "/api": use raw
  else: append "/api" to raw (strip trailing "/")
```

```text
apiRequest(endpoint, options):
  token = localStorage["token"]

  headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    if token: "Authorization": "Bearer <token>",
    ...options.headers
  }

  response = fetch(API_URL + endpoint, { ...options, headers })
  data = parse JSON

  if !response.ok:
    throw Error(data.message or "Something went wrong")

  return data
```

```text
authService:
  register(userData):
    resp = apiRequest("/auth/register", POST JSON userData)
    if resp.success and resp.data.token:
      save token
    return resp

  login(credentials):
    resp = apiRequest("/auth/login", POST JSON credentials)
    if resp.success and resp.data.token:
      save token
    return resp

  getCurrentUser():
    return apiRequest("/auth/me", GET)

  logout():
    remove token

  forgotPassword(email):
    return apiRequest("/auth/forgot-password", POST { email })
```

```text
passwordService:
  changePassword(passwordData):
    return apiRequest("/auth/change-password", PUT passwordData)
```

### Chatbot Service (Frontend)

```text
sendChatMessage(message, history = [], mode = "mental-support", file = null):
  if file exists:
    formData = new FormData()
    formData["message"] = message
    formData["conversationHistory"] = JSON.stringify(history)
    formData["mode"] = mode
    formData["file"] = file

    token = localStorage["token"]
    base = env.VITE_API_URL or "http://localhost:5000/api"

    response = fetch(base + "/chatbot/chat", {
      method: "POST",
      headers: { "Authorization": "Bearer <token>" }, // no Content-Type
      body: formData
    })
    data = JSON
    if !response.ok: throw Error(data.message or "API request failed")
    return data

  else:
    return apiRequest("/chatbot/chat", POST {
      message,
      conversationHistory: history,
      mode
    })

getAvailableModels():
  return apiRequest("/chatbot/models", GET)
```

### Key Pages (High-Level)

```text
Home:
  show marketing sections (hero, features, modules, pricing, resources)
  provide CTAs to login/signup

Login/Signup:
  capture credentials / registration data
  call authService.login or authService.register
  on success:
    authContext.login(user, token, firstLogin)
    redirect based on role to "/dashboard"

UserDashboard:
  fetch student-specific data (tasks, quizzes, resources, activity)
  render overview cards and navigation links

MentorDashboard:
  fetch mentors list of students/groups and recent activity
  allow mentor actions (e.g., group or resource management)

AdminDashboard:
  call /api/admin/stats and /api/admin/mentors
  display counts of students/mentors/admins
  allow creating mentors (form -> POST /api/admin/mentors)

ChatPage:
  maintain conversation history in state
  when user sends message or uploads PDF:
    call sendChatMessage()
    append bot response to history

ResumePage / ATSScorePage:
  let user build or upload resume
  send data to backend chatbot/ATS services
  render feedback and ATS score

ResourcesPage / WellnessPage / StudyGroupsPage / AchievementsPage / EditProfile:
  call corresponding backend endpoints
  render lists, detail views, and forms for updates
```

